EXPLANATION – Matter in bolded italics is new; matter between brackets [omitted material] is material to be omitted.
AN ACT relating to Medicaid; requiring the Director of the Department of Health
and Human Services to seek to establish certain rates of reimbursement
under Medicaid for vagus nerve stimulation therapy devices , [and]
replacement parts for such a device [;] and the procedures necessary
to implant, repair or replace a part of such a device; and providing
other matters properly relating thereto.
Legislative Counsel’s Digest:
1 Existing law requires the Department of Health and Human Services to administer the
2 Medicaid program. (NRS 422.270) This bill requires the Director of the Department to submit
3 to the United States Secretary of Health and Human Services a request to amend Medicaid to
4 provide rates of reimbursement greater than or equal to 82 percent of the cost for : (1) a
5 vagus nerve stimulation therapy device [or] ; (2) any replacement [parts] part for such a
6 device [that are greater than or equal to 82 percent of the cost of such a device or replacement
7 parts, as applicable.] ; and (3) the procedure necessary to implant, repair or replace a part
8 of such a device. This bill also clarifies that [such] the rates of reimbursement established
9 for the cost of a vagus nerve stimulation therapy device and any replacement part for
10 such a device must be separate from and in addition to the rates of reimbursement for medical
11 care necessary for the implantation or repair of such a device or the replacement of a part for
12 the device.
THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF NEVADA, REPRESENTED IN
SENATE AND ASSEMBLY, DO ENACT AS FOLLOWS:
1 Section 1. 1. On or before October 1, 2025, the Director of the Department
2 of Health and Human Services shall submit to the United States Secretary of Health
3 and Human Services a request to include under Medicaid:
4 (a) A rate of reimbursement for a vagus nerve stimulation therapy device that
5 is greater than or equal to 82 percent of the cost of such a device; [and]

