1 (b) A rate of reimbursement for any replacement part for a vagus nerve
2 stimulation therapy device that is greater than or equal to 82 percent of the cost of
3 such a replacement part [.] ; and
4 (c) A rate of reimbursement for the procedure necessary to implant,
5 repair or replace a part of a vagus nerve stimulation therapy device that is
6 greater than or equal to 82 percent of the cost of the procedure.
7 2. The rates of reimbursement established pursuant to paragraphs (a) and
8 (b) of subsection 1 must be separate from and in addition to the rates of
9 reimbursement for the medical care necessary for implantation or repair of a vagus
10 nerve stimulation therapy device or the replacement of a part for such a device.
11 3. The request submitted pursuant to subsection 1 must be supported using
12 methods for determining rates of reimbursement accepted by the Secretary.
13 Sec. 2. This act becomes effective upon passage and approval.

